<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/671b: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-21">May 21,
                                    1940</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>55. After consulting offices in Switzerland please cable whether
                                American citizens are able to proceed promptly to Genoa from
                                Switzerland for embarkation United States. Is there any difficulty
                                in obtaining Swiss exit visas or Italian entrance and exit
                                visas?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>